<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,541,926]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" box="[322,370,577,600]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haminoeidae" genus="Atys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,370,577,600]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">Atys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Montfort, D. de" box="[642,825,577,602]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref20196" refString="Montfort, D. de (1810) Conchyliologie systematique, et classification methodique des coquilles. Coquilles Univalves, non cloisonnees. Vol. 2. F. Schoell, Paris, 676 pp." type="book" year="1810">Montfort (1810)</bibRefCitation>
with 
<typeStatus box="[889,937,578,602]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Montfort, 1810" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" box="[1032,1376,577,602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haminoeidae" genus="Atys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cymbulus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1194,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">Atys cymbulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Montfort, D. de" box="[1201,1376,577,602]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref20196" refString="Montfort, D. de (1810) Conchyliologie systematique, et classification methodique des coquilles. Coquilles Univalves, non cloisonnees. Vol. 2. F. Schoell, Paris, 676 pp." type="book" year="1810">Montfort, 1810</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[578,914,613,638]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bullidae" genus="Bulla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="naucum">
<emphasis box="[578,734,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">Bulla naucum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[741,914,613,638]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref19503" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae. Editio Decima, Tomus I. Laurentii Salvii. Holmiae [Stockholm], 823 pp." type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pilsbry, H. A." box="[956,1119,613,638]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref20498" refString="Pilsbry, H. A. (1895) Manual of Conchology, structural and systematic. Vol. 15. Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, Philadelphia, 436 pp." type="book" year="1895">Pilsbry (1895)</bibRefCitation>
, and apparently even before by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sowerby, G. B." box="[186,369,649,674]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" pagination="1843 - 1878" refId="ref21194" refString="Sowerby, G. B. (1870) Monograph of the genus Atys. In: Reeve, L. A. (Ed.), Conchologica Iconica, or Illustrations of the shells of molluscous animals 1843 - 1878. Vol. 17. L. Reeve &amp; Co, London. [pages not numbered]" type="book chapter" year="1870">Sowerby (1870)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Montfort, D. de" box="[380,562,649,674]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref20196" refString="Montfort, D. de (1810) Conchyliologie systematique, et classification methodique des coquilles. Coquilles Univalves, non cloisonnees. Vol. 2. F. Schoell, Paris, 676 pp." type="book" year="1810">Montfort (1810)</bibRefCitation>
referred the species to the African coast, although he did not specify the exact locality; though, the author was likely referring to the east coast of Africa, because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1081,1201,686,709]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bullidae" genus="Bulla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="naucum">
<emphasis box="[1081,1201,686,709]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">A. naucum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known in the Indo-West Pacific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,541,926]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">
Species have been ascribed to this genus mostly based on shell morphology. The genus is characterized by umbilicate oval-elongate or inflated shells, with spiral grooves. The gizzard plates are covered with tiny rods and the radula has a median tooth (
<bibRefCitation author="Bergh, R." box="[523,663,829,854]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" pagination="159 - 382" refId="ref17880" refString="Bergh, R. (1901) Tectibranchia. Lophocercidae. Ascoglossa. In: Semper, C. (Ed.), Reisen im Archipel der Philippinen von Dr. C. Semper. Vol. 7. C. W. Kreidel, Wiesbaden, pp. 159 - 382." type="book chapter" year="1901">Bergh 1901</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lin, G. Y." box="[680,790,829,854]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref19471" refString="Lin, G. Y. (1997) Fauna Sinica: Phylum Mollusca, Class Gastropoda, Sub-Class Opisthobranchia, Order Cephalaspidea. Science Presss, Beijing, 246 pp." type="book" year="1997">Lin 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carlson, C. &amp; Hoff, P. J." box="[806,1062,829,854]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref18259" refString="Carlson, C. &amp; Hoff, P. J. (1999) Atys naucum gizzard plates. Accessed through: The Sea Slug Forum. Available from: http: // www. seaslugforum. net / find / 1704 (accessed 10 July 2010)" type="url" year="1999">Carlson &amp; Hoff 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" box="[1342,1390,830,853]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haminoeidae" genus="Atys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1342,1390,830,853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">Atys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are commonly found on shallow sandy bottoms in tropical and temperate regions and about 50 species have been reported in the Indo-West Pacific (
<bibRefCitation author="OBIS" box="[537,679,901,926]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" refId="ref20320" refString="OBIS (2012 a) Atys species. Accessed through: OBIS Indo Pacific Molluscan Database. Available from: http: // clade. ansp. org / obis / search. php / 67954 (accessed 5 July 2012)" type="url" year="2012">
<collectionCode box="[537,602,901,926]" pageId="13" pageNumber="368">OBIS</collectionCode>
2012a
</bibRefCitation>
) (see 
<tableCitation box="[746,815,901,926]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="21.[147,228,479,500]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="TABLE 2. Summary of most useful characters for diagnosis of species of Atys." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF456656FF9FA27FFF7CFE5AFC6168FE" pageId="13" pageNumber="368" tableUuid="DF456656FF9FA27FFF7CFE5AFC6168FE">Tab. 2</tableCitation>
for diagnostic characters of species described here).
</paragraph>
